TY  - JOUR
T1  - Systems of Exchange
AU  - Biggart, Nicole Woolsey
AU  - Delbridge, Rick
Y1  - 2004/01/01
PY  - 2004
DA  - 2004/01/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2004.11851707
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2004.11851707
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 28
EP  - 49
VL  - 29
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - We develop a classification scheme of systems of exchange using concepts from network analysis, economics, and cultural sociology. This classification illustrates that the ?free market? is but one possible type of economy and that other types are not best understood as imperfections. This classification helps to distinguish analytically among qualitatively different types of exchange arrangements and suggests bases from which to develop theories about the organization of markets and exchange systems of various types.
AB  - We develop a classification scheme of systems of exchange using concepts from network analysis, economics, and cultural sociology. This classification illustrates that the ?free market? is but one possible type of economy and that other types are not best understood as imperfections. This classification helps to distinguish analytically among qualitatively different types of exchange arrangements and suggests bases from which to develop theories about the organization of markets and exchange systems of various types.
SN  - 0363-7425
M3  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2004.11851707
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/amr.2004.11851707
